to the editor re why the writer is last to know by martin arnold making books column july 25 that book publishers do not disclose to their authors information like sales and advertising budgets is indeed unfortunate the bigger tragedy occurs when authors who teach mfa programs in creative writing do n't tell their students that such a situation is likely to await them should they get published heaven forbid that considerations of business infiltrate the sacred halls where art is produced the book publishers are not the only people keeping writers in the dark good for martin arnold for shedding light timothy s lemire boston july 25 2002

